inn1.comm: stays over the wicket to the left hander who squeezes a full and swinging delivery out to square and they're off the mark immediately
bangs in short, some swing away, Watson squares behind it, the outside edge not carrying to second slip, bouncing just in front. Some immediate encouragement for West Indies and Edwards, however
good ball, some decent carry and at 85.2mph, nips away off the seam after pitching on a good length and the batsman quickly draws his bat in
again some good pace and carry off the deck, it's left as it comes in on a good length
fired again across him, flatter this time, left alone
on off stump, defended on the front foot into the covers with a slight push and they decide not to run
some movement off the seam back in to the right hander, Powell generating plenty of awkward bounce. In the end it's tucked down off the hips in line with off
shortish ball on off, coming across him, the batsman caught in two minds shaping initially for the pull and ends up stopping on the shot
gets hold of the pull this time! Just a fraction short from Powell and Marsh is so quick to tranfer his weight and send it fairly aerial - deliberately - and straight through square
hustles up to him now, the ball slanting across him and the batsman shapes to cut but it goes through
stifled appeal but the batsman had got some bat on to it as he tried to squeeze to square - the ball also pitched outside leg
short and cut hard off the back foot through point. The shot was there for the making
some width outside off, driven straight to the man at cover
big width outside off, cut down without much power, into the turf and on towards first slip, Gayle putting both hands above his head and parrying it down
fired flat and hard down the channel, Watson looks to cut but the ball deceives him as it nips back in off the seam and goes over the blade
some swing outside off and down the channel, probing once more and beating Watson again who offers the shot off the back foot, stuck in his crease - no footwork of which to speak
strays on to the legs now and Watson breaks the shackles with a strong clip off the legs through square
on the legs once more and again it's turned off the legs for some more easy runs
some movement away off the seam, good pace and carry, the batsman shoulders arms
some late swing, the ball starting outside the legs and carrying back in and it's whipped off the legs behind square
on the legs again and turned out firmly to deep square and they will collect just the single
a good leave from Watson, the ball coming back in from just outside off, shouldering arms and letting it go through
nipped back in from outside off, pushed into the covers and they run well through
tapped away to short midwicket on the legs
carries slickly through across him, Marsh's feet stuck in the crease as he's caught in two minds whether to go forward or back
oh! Just wide of the diving man at point, Marshall, but it's a no-ball as well and so up comes the free hit
short on the legs and he stands tall and almost-Hayden-like, he shoulders the ball through midwicket
width outside off, cuts hard off the back foot, a good diving effort on the third man boundary by Miller, the left-hand spinner running round from his left
outside off, some big width and he climbs into a hard cut off the back foot in front of point
round the wicket now, and played back down into the turf
low full toss, driven to the covers
oh, full delivery and he drives an inside edge on to the pads, in the air a while and falls just short of gully who dived forward
driven on the front foot into the covers now
width outside off, cut down into the track and out towards point
banged in short, pulled round to short fine leg, the batsman not quite getting hold of it, playing too late on the shot
on the front foot, driven out to short midwicket. He's looking quite scratchy today, Watson, there were a few play-and-misses earlier off Edwards
tucked off to point on the front foot
width outside off, leans and cut down towards backward point
a half-volley, put away with a firm push through mid-off, Warson did very well to jump over the ball as he was nutmegged and the ball went all the way
tucked off the legs out to short midwicket
defended on the front foot
short ball outside off, pulled straight and flat and hard to mid-on where it just pitched in front of the fielder Findlay who was quickly on his knees
outside off, a false shot now, trying to pull it across the line
stays over the wicket and pushes it well past the outside edge, the ball moving away off the seam and the batsman playing right inside the line
outside off, pushed down and they jog through
pushed on the front foot straight to mid on
width outside off, gets down on one knee and eases it behind point
full ball on leg, wristed out to short midwicket on the front foot
outside off, played out to point off the back foot this time
defended on the front foot
on off, pulled out to short midwicket
played forward now
flat-pulled out to mid off
short ball and pulled through square
played forward and they jog through
squeezed off the legs in line with middle and turned behind square
full ball outside off, pushed into the covers defensively
on middle, pushed forward defensively and a loud call of "No!" comes in lest there have been any doubt
outside off and he opens the face to run the ball through third man, the ball coming off a thick outside edge of the shoulder of the bat
outside off, looks to pull it round, but an under edge bounces way in front of the keeper, having deviated back in just past off stump
outside off, the batsman shoulders arms
turned off the legs to short midwicket
played on the front foot
shoulders arms and lets the ball go flat and wide across him
big width outside off, the batsman works it out hard through extra cover
on the legs, gets right over it and wrists it down to fine leg
played down off the back foot to third man
scooped with some impressive wrists out to deep midwicket, almost stopping on the shot
outside off and pulled hard to midwicket
played hard on the front foot
drives out to mid on, dragged away again
slower ball on the legs, driven out to mid on and they run through hard
tucked down off the back foot in line with off, good slower delivery to end the over
defended forward and they charge through
outside off, played back down forward
down leg, and tried to turn it round and Bravo grimaces in follow through, in some discomfort
on middle, pushes it out in front of midwicket
big width outside off, cut off the back foot down to third man and Powell comes round and takes the catch
off the mark straight away with a turn off the legs to deep backward square leg
pushed off the legs to midwicket
stifled appeal, perhaps drifting down leg, Ronchi brushing off the legs
defended back down into the covers
nipped back in off the seam, played down, he thinks he's bowled him, but the ball crashes into the turf and bounces right over the sticks
nipped back in from outside off, pushed into the covers once more
outside off and worked away well through midwicket
width outside off, cut into the covers
shoulders arms and lets this one go through
slashes hard at a cut, the ball goes through
outside off, the batsman shoulders arms
width again, outside off, squeezed into the covers and the throw comes in hard at the non-striker's end but even a direct hit wouldn't have caused too many problems for the third umpire
driven out to mid on
on the front foot, pushed into the covers, some hesitation in the running
outside off and great shot from Ronchi, lifting it over mid off and it goes aerial
pushed into the covers
outside off, and there he goes again! Lifts it off the bottom of the bat once more, all shoulders in the straight drive
outside off, pushes it down
once more he goes! The third six of the over, launching off the bottom of the bat yet again and over long off it goes, the ball going fairly flat. Caught well by the sightscreen attendant in the deep
driven down the ground on the front foot
some width outside off, cut at it and played right over
outside off, let it go through
once more, lets it go through
outside off, pushed into the covers
driven to the covers and they run through well
pushed up there in line with off, defended on the front foot
a quick single through again
short and straight and the batsman is quick to duck down. Some good aggression from Edwards
on middle and it's lifted again, straight once more, a clean hit high and dipping just over the rope
down the legs and he can't quite adjust his shoulders in the pull to deep square leg
short ball, clubbed away, this time right over long on to bring up his fifth six from a mere 16 deliveries
width outside off, backs away, looking for it again and his cut scythes only fresh air and he quickly has a laugh at himself
the batsman drops it down and they run through quickly
comes out on the legs, pushes out on the legs and they will have to be quick if they want two
outside off, cut into the covers now
round the wicket, on to the legs and pulled hard through square and a wayward return
outside off, opens up the face and that's a tremendous shot
back over the head of the bowler this time and he's raining down the blows
on the legs, flicked away to the legs and they run through the second
outside off, chased the ball away from his body, and a thick snick is pouched gratefully by the keeper
off the mark immediately with a tuck off the legs behind square
outside off, a strong drive through the covers to bring up his fifty which is roundly applauded by his team-mates. It's the equal second-fastest ODI fifty by an Australian
outside off, pushed to point and there's a bark of "Wait on!"
banged in hard, the batsman bends his back and shapes to cut and there's yet another no-ball from the bowler
outside off and that's just special, backs away and somehow muscles it over long off, it's gone a long way
a very wide down off
full pitched now, defended on the front foot
outside off, pushed into the covers and they run through
on the front foot, pushed to mid on and a pumped-up pair look to squeeze out the single but that would have been calamitous from their point of view
on middle, driven off the legs with a closed bat face, a flick really, out to midwicket
outside off, driven well through the covers and Ronchi collects another boundary
driven straight and hard out to long on and some great fielding in the deep by Findlay, diving to his left

and the change pays immediate dividends! The stands erupt and there are muted, relieved smiles from the players as he draws him forward and he steers an edge to Ramdin who takes a lowish catch at the third attempt
outside off, squeezed to the covers and he too is off the mark straight away
round the wicket now, defended back down the line
stays round, up there on off, defended back forward
outside off, presents a firm face with a defensive towards the covers
backs away to give himself room to drive out to mid off
Sarwan breaks through with his first ball, too! Clarke backs away to try to cut out to point, but takes a faint outside edge - though one which was obvious enough - and Ramdin snaps it up
outside off, popped up a touch out towards midwicket, accompanied by a shout of "Catch it, Crystal" direct at Gayle there
defended on the front foot
again defended, Sarwan coming round the wicket here
more defence, some good control from Sarwan here
pitches back in towards him and driven back forward
outside off, some turn back in and the batsman plays with the spin, working it out to square
outside off, played back down the line off the back foot
defended back down the line
on the back foot, squeezed out to the gully
keeps him quiet yet again, Symonds defending down off the back foot
outside off, pushed into the covers
some turn back in from outside off, and worked with the spin, pulling it to square
forces the front-foot defensive this time
on the legs, defended on the front foot out to midwicket, Gayle insouciantly ignoring Ramdin's shout to "Attack, Crystal", strolling to pick it up
defended on the front foot
played on the front foot out to mid off now
outside off, pushed on the front foot just behind point
defended back down the line
driven back to the bowler who dives and stops
pushed out to the covers
Symonds steers off the crouch to point
good power and placement from Symonds, backing away and waiting for the short and loose one which he peels off through point with a cut
on the front foot now and pushed to the covers
pushed on the front foot back to the bowler
defended on the front foot again
on the legs, a leading edge as he tries to turn it to the legs, Chanderpaul takes it, no chance of a run and he flicks it back, wide of the bowler, allowing overthrows (or overflicks)
played on the front foot
turned off the legs this time
steps out on the front foot and defends forward
on the front foot, defended down without too much trouble
pushed into the covers on the front foot
width outside off, turned back in a touch, worked into the covers
outside off, pushed down to the gully and they seek the single
on the front foot, driven straight to the man at cover
dug out towards mid on
driven out tamely to long on
driven out to long on
squeezes out a drive to long on
gets right over in defence
outside off again and pushes to point
outside off, cut hard to point
played forward
outside off again, opens the face and runs it down behind point, Bravo doing very well on the boundary with the slide and stop
defended forward
"Catch it!" goes the cry, in vain
outside off, turns back in and is worked out off the back foot
on the front foot, defended back down in line with off on the front foot
outside off, pushed out to point and they push for two and get them easily enough
on to the legs, pulled round hard to square
defended forward
outside off, pushed out to midwicket
on the front foot, pushed out to mid off
on the legs, driven out to long on
defended on the front foot out to mid off
width outside off, driven into the covers
defended on the front foot
defended down the line on the back foot
outside off, let it go through
played off the back foot to mid off
outside off, turned back in, and fended down off the back foot
some width outside off and driven well through the covers
on the front foot, pushed out to short midwicket
on the front foot, pushed out forward
outside off, pushed off the legs to midwicket
worked out forward
defended on the front foot in line with off
the lap sweep round to backward square leg now
defended on the front foot
worked on the front foot to short midwicket
on the front foot again, driven out to mid on
in on middle, wristed out to short midwicket
driven out to mid on
outside off and deftly cut down to third man, just opening the face and running it down
on the legs and lofted now out to midwicket
on the legs, pulled round in front of square
on the legs, pushed out to square
on the front foot, pushed to the covers
outside off, squeezed out to the legs
on the legs, pushed to fine leg
on the front foot, pushed out to the covers
attempted reverse sweep gpes awry
pushed back out towards the bowler who runs round
waits on the back foot and plays it at the top of the bounce with a push-drive to mid on
swept round to backward square leg
pushed off the legs to fine leg, they have to hurry but the throw comes in at the non-striker's end, deflects off naughtily and the batsmen steal the extra
outside the legs from over the wicket, swept round
on the legs and pulled hard out to midwicket
pushed forward
turned off the legs to square
on the front foot, driven out to short midwicket where Gayle tidies up
Gayle's in on the action again with a work out there
they take the single this time with a dab into the covers
outside off, turned in a touch, and worked back out to square
defended on the front foot
width outside off, cut off the back foot to gully
some width down the channel, but plenty of encouraging lift, the batsman goes to cut it and gets right under the ball
nipped back in off the seam, the batsman pushes it on to midwicket and they charge through
pushed across him, opened the face down to third man
outside off, cut down off the back foot to third man
defended back down the line
on the legs, pushes forward and moves the ball to midwicket
pushed to the covers on the front foot
down the ground and Symonds sends this one all the way, a loft over long on for a big six, Miller just dropping short
pushed into the covers and there's a chase again
worked down off the back foot through third man
on the legs, pushed down through the 45 off the pads
pushed off the legs to square
pushed forward
outside off, cut down off the back foot to third man who scrambles round to retrieve
banged across him, the ball rising and he steers it down to fine leg off the back foot
short ball, rising through to the keeper, the batsman backs away and looks to cut off the back foot
comes in in line with off, driven out straight to long on
outside off, cut down through backward point
worked out forward
down the ground, hoicked out to long on with a deliberate hit across the line - and they come back for the second - not too short of Miller on the boundary
short and pulled up towards midwicket, the ball hangs in the air for a while but nobody can get to it and Symonds' fifty has come up from 71 balls with three fours
outside off, cut to point
on middle, Symonds rocks back and cuts out to deep cover where Bravo retrieves it well
overpitched on off, driven back down the ground straight out to long off
over the wicket, slower one, Gayle is casually sloppy in the covers and lets through the single
driven straight down the ground
outside off, backs away and chops down into the ground off the back foot
outside off, backs away and cuts to the covers
outside off, pushed into the covers
full toss outside off, carved away hard with a cut off the back foot, Symonds giving himself plenty of room
pulls this one very hard behind square
on middle and leg, a touch short, again Symonds goes hard at it but his timing's not quite right and Chanderpaul tidies up
outside off, driven out to extra cover
short on the legs, pulled hard round through backward square leg. That would have been a wide if Symonds left it, instead the batsman decided to capitalise
got him this time! Symonds backs away once more, looking for the cut on a slightly slower one, instead the edge goes straight through to the keeper
pushed forward to mid off and they will have to hurry! Oh, but they're safe now
eased out to mid on with a front-foot drive
on the legs, pushed it out to point this time, the ball coming off the edge
outside off, cut hard out to point
on the legs, turned out to deep square and they come back for two - a better throw could have had Michael in trouble
driven out to long off to bring up a well-worked fifty with only three fours
on off, wristed out to wide mid on
driven to the covers and they pick up a quick single
outside off, cut down off the back foot to third man

slower ball and oh! That's hit the stumps! But the bail's not come off. Remarkable, an inside edge into the ground then thuds into the off stump which stays on, defiantly. Must have had glue on the bails or something...
outside off, short, and pulled behind square, Fletcher running round, misses it, and clatters into a rogue spectator
pushed forward, they take a cheeky single, Edwards runs forward to look to throw down the stumps
stays over the wicket, fires in full on off, Hussey goes for the big drive and picks out Findlay just inside long on, the fielder taking a good catch, jumping and with fingers upwards, palms showing
full toss on the knees, driven out over long on and just past Marshall's dive, the fielder nearly landing on a heavy bit of machinery - the roller. Could have been painful
outside off, cut out to point
on the legs, pushed out and commands to "Wait, wait"
full delivery, dug out and foisted back towards the bowler
outside off, cut back to the bowler, who goes out towards mid on and then his throw spooned out of his arm as he dived and they manage to take an overthrow (or underthrow, as it turned out)
outside off, cut hard through the covers, a clean shot and Bravo isn't happy with the end of that over to say the least
driven out to mid on
slipped out a full toss on to the legs and the batsman goes for the crashing pull which is top-edged aerially down fine leg
again angled down the leg side with a full toss, four more as there's an easy pull through backward square
backs away, well behind the stumps and drives out to the covers
goes for the reverse sweep and connects very well indeed, with a firm, well-struck shot behind square
on the legs, and on one knee, swept down
full toss above the hips on leg and that's crashingly pulled in front of square. It looked like Bravo was aiming for the yorker there
help-yourself stuff now, Hopes down on one knee and drives hard over long on
outside off, cut well off the back foot to deep cover
oh, just misses the off stump as Hopes backed away to give himself some room to cut
outside off, driven out to mid off
low full toss, Hussey backs away and deposits the ball high and far over straight long off
on the legs, driven up and over towards long on, didn't really get hold of that one
outside off and Hussey goes large again, this time lifting it hard and flat over long on
width outside leg now and beefed hard and high between long on and deep midwicket
shocking. Hang your head in shame, Andre Fletcher. Hussey sends it high and without much power, and he's already walking off thinking he's definitely out, but Fletcher fluffed it big time
but Powell makes no mistake at deep backward square leg this time, the fielder coming round and having to reach away from his body with two hands at the last second

Fletcher makes amends this time with a much tougher catch than the sitter he dropped two balls ago, Hopes lifting up the ball towards wide mid-on and Fletcher dives forward to take it at full stretch, this time to cheers

inn2.comm: Gayle goes after the first one outside off, slams it into the turf and it bounces over the stumps
Gayle slashes at this one but it's too wide outside off and is called as such by umpire Bucknor
left alone outside off this time
Gayle drives away from his body, it beats the bat and goes through to Ronchi
and Gayle gets off the mark with a well controlled drive off the back foot, it races away square through point and he gets himself a boundary
that's a cross-batted club from Gayle, it flies away along the ground to mid off, where Hopes does well to stop it and deflects the ball towards mid on
Marshall forward and defends towards cover
right on line immediately and it stays a touch low, Gayle defends
cut away square but straight to point

and Johnson does the job! It's on a good length and Gayle doesn't quite know whether to go back or forward, he gets a thick edge and Ronchi's great game continues as he dives to his left and takes a very good catch
Sarwan on the back foot to start, punches it away to cover
good way to get off the mark, Sarwan quickly onto a short ball with a bit of width and cuts forward of point for a boundary
angled across Sarwan, who leaves this one
Lee digs this one in, Marshall goes back and defends
Marshall forces this one off the back foot through point, a square drive really and it races away to the boundary
Lee probes outside off, Marshall blocks it away
pushed away defensively to point
Marshall forward and defends, Lee appeals for lbw and it might have flicked the top of the pad before rocketing off the middle of the bat, but certainly outside the line of off
a wild attempted drive from Marshall, who flashes outside off and sees the ball whizz past the bat

Sarwan crunches this one wide of point where Clarke makes a terrific diving stop, then turns and throws to the bowler's end where Sarwan was a long, long way short. Lucky for him, Clarke's throw was wide

and there's a very quick single, Marshall pushes to cover and scampers through. Symonds is the fielder, he under-arms it into the stumps at the bowler's end but Marshall gets home, you've got to be mighty fast to beat Symonds
another fast run as Sarwan pokes it to mid on, David Hussey's throw misses at the bowler's end
short and down leg side, so that's a wide
straight-bat defence this time, Johnson gets across to cut it off, another shy at the stumps, this time at the striker's end as Marshall was initially wanting a single, the throw missed though
Marshall drives at this one outside off, it beats the bat
on the pads and it's tucked away through midwicket for a single
on the back foot and punches this one to cover
straight ball this time, Marshall clips it away through square leg
dead on line again and it stays down a touch, Sarwan jumps then has to adjust and does well to get the bat down on this one
driven away to cover and they get a single
oh, there's a thick edge from Marshall and it falls just a few centimetres short of Watson at first slip. A stroke of luck for Marshall
forward and he defends this back down the pitch
driven off the back foot to cover and there's no run
Sarwan backs away and tries for an expansive cut, the shortish one from Johnson bounces a touch too much and beats the bat
another shortish ball, Sarwan looks to pull but mistimes it and the ball lobs just in front of mid on

excellent catch! Sarwan knows he has to get the runs flowing and drives on the up, but it's a slower ball and he doesn't quite time it, the ball looks like clearing James Hopes at mid off but he times his leap to perfection and snares it with both hands above his head
pushed into the off side, they can't manufacture a single
Chanderpaul gets off the mark deflecting this one behind point
down leg side and that's a wide, Lee doesn't think it should have been but every umpire will call those
short and on leg, Chanderpaul hooks and it flies over the short fine leg and away to the boundary
Chanderpaul looks to cut this one, it beats the bat
good ball, fuller length and nipping back in to the left-hander, Chanderpaul good enough to defend
excellent shot, Chanderpaul drives this one sweetly through the vacant cover region for four
doesn't quite get this one right as he attempts to repeat the shot, a thick inside egde races past the stumps
outside off, Marshall defends
well struck, this one is on the stumps and a half-volley, Chanderpaul simply lifts this one over midwicket and with the field up that's two bounces over the boundary
prodded away into the on side
outside off now, Chanderpaul cuts it away behind point
prodded away defensively to cover
dropped! Nathan Bracken puts this one down at short fine leg. Johnson puts it on the pads, Marshall flicks it on the up and Bracken crouches down and fumbles what he definitely should have taken
punched away through the off side
short and down leg side, that's a wide
driven hard to mid off, finds the fieldsman
clubbed straight down into the turf and through to Ronchi
Chanderpaul tries for a big drive, mistimes it though and it goes straight back to Lee
bad ball, Lee drags this one short and well down leg side
pulled away through midwicket and they get a couple
this one beats the bat, Chanderpaul looking to cut behind point and it gets a bit too close to him
guided away to gully
punched away towards point
good timing from Marshall, this one is right on line and driven straight back past the bowler
wide of off, he tries for a big drive but it's too wide
guided away behind point this time
driven to mid on
short outside off, Chanderpaul cuts in the air and it bounces away to third man
and a leading edge from Marshall just lobs over the bowler's head, a stroke of luck for Marshall
defended into the covers
outside off, late cut dropped by Watson at second slip position, clutch-diving to his right
outside off, cuts right over it
defended down off
turned into the leg side on the front foot
again turned off the legs to fine
some lift there, and defended back down off the back foot
on the legs, tucked out to midwicket
turned off the legs in front of square this time
full toss down the legs, put away with a firm pull through the 45 this time
defended back down the line
a huge appeal for one which looks straightforward enough and Umpire Ruaf doesn't need much time to adjudge that one was going on - to hit the leg stump according to Hawk-Eye
outside off, cut down behind point
outside off, pushed off the back foot into the covers
pushed to the covers
on the legs, bends over, and works it square
width outside off and some swing away, probably just about gets away with that one
on middle and off, the batsman strides down and brushes to square
pushed back down the line towards straight mid off
pitches outside off, some movement away, the batsman shoulders arms as it's on a good length
some width outside leg, tucked away behind square
outside off, cut to point
outside off, pushed down to third man
on the legs, pushed off to square
outside off, cut into the covers
tucked off the legs
outside off, driven on the front foot to the covers
outside off, pushed down without trouble
on the front foot, driven out to mid on
pushed forward
pushed across him, played down on the back foot to the covers
outside off, cut down off the back foot to third man
defended again on the front foot
turned off the legs to square
outside off, edged away - thickishly and forcefully - and the ball races through third man
full delivery, lands on the toes in line with off, pushed forward straight
wristed off the legs to square
on the front foot, driven out to long on
on the legs, turned square
outside off, cut to backward point
outside off, cut to point
played out square
on the legs, pushed out to midwicket
pushed off the legs through midwicket
on the back foot outside off, pushed out to the covers
flicked off the legs and snapped up by Lee at backward square leg, Lee's not sure if he caught it or not
defended back down straight in line with off
defended on the front foot
turned off the legs
outside off, cut through backward point
outside off, cut away off the back foot
width outside off, worked out behind point
on middle, driven back out to long on
outside off, pushed to point
outside off, driven to wide mid on
slanted across him, the batsman thinks about playing, and indeed dabs at it, his feet rooted to the crease, and the ball goes over
on middle and off, wristed off to square
on the legs, pulled round to square
stays over the wicket, a straightish line up there on off, defended forward
outside off, wristed towards the bowler who stops it with two hands to the left
driven out to the covers
pushed back to the bowler
super catch from Lee, Chanderpaul offers the skier, and Lee sets himself at long off to receive, palms upwards, and tumbles back with the momentum, but the ball pouched safely
defended on the front foot back in line with off
outside off, the batsman takes one step to think about it, before pulling out
defended on the front foot
defended on the front foot
defended on th e back foot now
on middle, turned out to midwicket
round the wicket, pushes it down off, the batsman shoulders arms
width outside off, cut out to point
width again outside off, cut to point once more
round the wicket, pushes it up on the toes, and it's accordingly pushed out to the covers
pushed into the covers again
an edge outside off
big width outside off, cut out to deep point
outside off, throws his hands and shoulders at that one, but doesn't quite connect
on off, pulled round in front of midwicket and goes on to towards the rope
width outside off - too much for the umpire's liking
Symonds is employing spin today, by the way, and now it's up there on off, defended on the front foot
moved to short midwicket
pushed on the front foot to the covers
width outside off, driven up and over towards the covers
round the wicket now, some width outside off, the batsman plays it into the covers
pushed up there and it goes on with the arm, the batsman defends down without too much trouble
pushed off the legs and they think of coming back for the second
outside off, kneels down and deposits very straight over long off
driven hard through the covers now
pushed across him on to off, played back out forward
